Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.12,0:00:04.45,Default,,0,0,0,,During his earthly ministry, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.45,0:00:06.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus miraculously healed \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.46,0:00:08.99,Default,,0,0,0,,many sick or disabled persons. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.99,0:00:11.29,Default,,0,0,0,,At times, \Nhe would say to such ones \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.29,0:00:15.23,Default,,0,0,0,,the expression we find \Nat Matthew 9:29: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.23,0:00:20.24,Default,,0,0,0,,“According to your faith \Nlet it happen to you.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.24,0:00:22.54,Default,,0,0,0,,The principle of what Jesus stated \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.54,0:00:27.08,Default,,0,0,0,,applies in every aspect \Nof our Christian life and ministry. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.08,0:00:30.61,Default,,0,0,0,,But today we will discuss how this principle \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.61,0:00:33.55,Default,,0,0,0,,that faith in Jehovah makes things happen \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.55,0:00:35.55,Default,,0,0,0,,can work for us in three areas. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.55,0:00:37.55,Default,,0,0,0,,We will see: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.55,0:00:42.39,Default,,0,0,0,,1) how our faith has made positive things \Nhappen in our personal life, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.39,0:00:46.50,Default,,0,0,0,,2) how we can accomplish \Nthings in God’s service \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.50,0:00:51.63,Default,,0,0,0,,that would not be possible \Nwithout faith in Jehovah God, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.63,0:00:56.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and 3) how faith moves us \Nto step out of our comfort zone \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.51,0:00:59.84,Default,,0,0,0,,to do more in Jehovah’s service.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.84,0:01:03.75,Default,,0,0,0,,The principle that faith in Jehovah \Nmakes things happen \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.75,0:01:07.95,Default,,0,0,0,,is well illustrated in one \Nof the miracles Jesus performed. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.95,0:01:12.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Please open your Bible to Mark chapter 5, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.12,0:01:16.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and let’s read verses 25-29: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.03,0:01:18.43,Default,,0,0,0,,“Now there was a woman \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.43,0:01:21.97,Default,,0,0,0,,“who had had \Na flow of blood for 12 years. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.97,0:01:25.57,Default,,0,0,0,,“She had suffered much \Nat the hands of many physicians \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.57,0:01:28.10,Default,,0,0,0,,“and had spent all her resources, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.10,0:01:31.81,Default,,0,0,0,,“and she was no better but, \Nrather, had become worse. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.81,0:01:35.78,Default,,0,0,0,,“When she heard \Nthe reports about Jesus, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.78,0:01:40.58,Default,,0,0,0,,“she came up behind him in the crowd \Nand touched his outer garment, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.58,0:01:42.99,Default,,0,0,0,,“for she kept saying: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.99,0:01:47.72,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘If I touch just his outer garments, \NI will get well.’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.72,0:01:51.96,Default,,0,0,0,,“And immediately her flow \Nof blood dried up, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.96,0:01:54.06,Default,,0,0,0,,“and she sensed in her body \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.06,0:01:58.47,Default,,0,0,0,,that she had been healed \Nof the grievous sickness.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.47,0:02:02.67,Default,,0,0,0,,In the following verses, \NJesus asked who had touched him. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.67,0:02:04.67,Default,,0,0,0,,The woman then revealed \Nbefore the crowd \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.67,0:02:07.98,Default,,0,0,0,,what she had done \Nand how she’d been cured. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.98,0:02:12.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Now notice Jesus’ response in verse 34: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.52,0:02:15.12,Default,,0,0,0,,“He said to her: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.12,0:02:18.89,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘Daughter, \Nyour faith has made you well. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.89,0:02:21.32,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘Go in peace, and be healed\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.32,0:02:23.46,Default,,0,0,0,,from your grievous sickness.’”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.46,0:02:25.46,Default,,0,0,0,,What comforting words \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.46,0:02:27.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus spoke to this trembling woman: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.83,0:02:30.83,Default,,0,0,0,,“Your faith has made you well.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.83,0:02:32.84,Default,,0,0,0,,What did Jesus mean? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.84,0:02:36.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s examine the account more closely.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.27,0:02:40.58,Default,,0,0,0,,It says that the woman \Nheard “reports about Jesus.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.58,0:02:42.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Many others heard the same reports, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.85,0:02:45.15,Default,,0,0,0,,but not all put faith in Jesus. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.15,0:02:47.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And think of the circumstances \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.58,0:02:51.15,Default,,0,0,0,,that could have prevented her \Nfrom even coming to Jesus. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.15,0:02:53.82,Default,,0,0,0,,She had been disappointed many times \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.82,0:02:55.99,Default,,0,0,0,,over the past 12 years. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.99,0:02:57.99,Default,,0,0,0,,She might well have thought: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.99,0:03:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,‘What’s the use? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.00,0:03:03.20,Default,,0,0,0,,‘I’m tired and weak and poor. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.20,0:03:05.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m staying home.’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.20,0:03:07.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Or ‘I would like for Jesus to see me, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.80,0:03:09.97,Default,,0,0,0,,‘but there is such a crowd. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.97,0:03:12.24,Default,,0,0,0,,‘How will I ever get through to him? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.24,0:03:15.95,Default,,0,0,0,,‘And after all, \NI’m in an unclean state, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.95,0:03:18.01,Default,,0,0,0,,‘and if the people discover this, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.01,0:03:20.02,Default,,0,0,0,,perhaps they will punish me.’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.02,0:03:23.49,Default,,0,0,0,,No, she did not allow \Nthese negative thoughts \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.49,0:03:25.99,Default,,0,0,0,,or doubts to fill her mind. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.99,0:03:27.99,Default,,0,0,0,,She left her home. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.99,0:03:31.39,Default,,0,0,0,,She found Jesus \Ndespite the large crowd. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.39,0:03:33.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And what was she saying? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.43,0:03:35.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Did she say, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.43,0:03:37.73,Default,,0,0,0,,“If I touch just his outer garments, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.73,0:03:40.04,Default,,0,0,0,,maybe I will get well”? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.04,0:03:42.04,Default,,0,0,0,,No, she said, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.04,0:03:44.04,Default,,0,0,0,,“I will get well.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.04,0:03:46.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, it was not the case \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.74,0:03:48.88,Default,,0,0,0,,that her faith healed her. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.88,0:03:53.05,Default,,0,0,0,,No, but her faith moved her \Nto come to Jesus, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.05,0:03:55.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and she was healed \Nby the power from Jehovah \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.85,0:03:58.05,Default,,0,0,0,,that flowed through his Son. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.05,0:04:00.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Faith to approach Jesus \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.52,0:04:03.93,Default,,0,0,0,,made it happen for her.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.93,0:04:07.06,Default,,0,0,0,,If you are a dedicated, \Nbaptized Christian, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.06,0:04:10.40,Default,,0,0,0,,don’t you agree \Nthat your faith has already made \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.40,0:04:13.24,Default,,0,0,0,,positive things happen \Nin your personal life? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.24,0:04:16.31,Default,,0,0,0,,No, you were not miraculously healed \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.31,0:04:18.34,Default,,0,0,0,,of your physical sicknesses. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.34,0:04:20.98,Default,,0,0,0,,We look forward \Nto physical healing of our ills \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.98,0:04:23.65,Default,,0,0,0,,during the Thousand Year Reign of Christ. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.65,0:04:27.35,Default,,0,0,0,,But today Jesus Christ directs a program \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.35,0:04:29.62,Default,,0,0,0,,of spiritual healing. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.62,0:04:32.56,Default,,0,0,0,,When we were a part \Nof this godless world, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.56,0:04:36.79,Default,,0,0,0,,many of us were sick spiritually, \Nmorally, and emotionally. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.79,0:04:38.93,Default,,0,0,0,,No one could cure us. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.93,0:04:43.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps we desperately \Ntried material things or pleasures \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.53,0:04:45.60,Default,,0,0,0,,to fill our spiritual need, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.60,0:04:48.71,Default,,0,0,0,,but our condition only got worse. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.71,0:04:51.64,Default,,0,0,0,,We were helpless and hopeless. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.64,0:04:54.78,Default,,0,0,0,,But then we heard “reports”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.78,0:04:58.51,Default,,0,0,0,,—the good news \Nof God’s Kingdom under Christ! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.51,0:05:00.52,Default,,0,0,0,,We studied the Bible. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.52,0:05:04.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Our faith moved us \Nto make positive changes in our life \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.69,0:05:07.99,Default,,0,0,0,,and to associate \Nwith the Christian congregation. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.99,0:05:12.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Today, we enjoy \Ngood spiritual health and happiness. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.66,0:05:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Our faith has made it happen.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.07,0:05:19.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Faith has also made it possible \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.37,0:05:22.01,Default,,0,0,0,,to accomplish things in God’s service \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.01,0:05:25.14,Default,,0,0,0,,that perhaps \Nwe never thought we could do. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.14,0:05:30.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Please open your Bibles \Nto Hebrews chapter 11. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.01,0:05:33.72,Default,,0,0,0,,In this portion \Nof Paul’s letter to the Hebrews, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.72,0:05:35.82,Default,,0,0,0,,he focuses on faith. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.82,0:05:39.22,Default,,0,0,0,,He begins with a definition of faith. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.22,0:05:41.96,Default,,0,0,0,,But then, starting in verse 4, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.96,0:05:45.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Paul acts as a sort of tour guide, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.03,0:05:47.03,Default,,0,0,0,,walking us through the corridor \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.03,0:05:49.97,Default,,0,0,0,,of thousands of years of Bible history. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.97,0:05:52.10,Default,,0,0,0,,He stops along the way \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.10,0:05:54.67,Default,,0,0,0,,to point out the extraordinary things \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.67,0:05:57.01,Default,,0,0,0,,that men and women of the past did \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.01,0:06:00.61,Default,,0,0,0,,by means of faith in Jehovah God. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.61,0:06:05.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Just glance down the columns \Nin this chapter \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.35,0:06:08.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and notice how Paul introduces \Neach paragraph \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.72,0:06:11.00,Default,,0,0,0,,with the words “by faith.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.56,0:06:15.39,Default,,0,0,0,,This expression “by faith” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.39,0:06:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,appears 18 times in this one chapter. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.73,0:06:22.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, when we look at the names \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.90,0:06:24.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Paul lists in this chapter, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.93,0:06:26.70,Default,,0,0,0,,we may think, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.70,0:06:30.04,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Well, these were spiritual “giants.”’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.04,0:06:33.74,Default,,0,0,0,,But in reality, \Nthey were ordinary humans \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.74,0:06:37.01,Default,,0,0,0,,with weaknesses \Nlike all of us have today. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.01,0:06:39.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The thing they all had in common \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.92,0:06:41.92,Default,,0,0,0,,was faith, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.92,0:06:44.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and faith in Jehovah \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.05,0:06:47.59,Default,,0,0,0,,made it possible \Nfor them to do amazing things. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.59,0:06:51.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s look at some of them \Nand compare what they did \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.13,0:06:54.03,Default,,0,0,0,,with what many of you \Nare doing today \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.03,0:06:56.07,Default,,0,0,0,,by faith.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.07,0:06:58.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s read verse 5: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.63,0:07:02.51,Default,,0,0,0,,“By faith Enoch was transferred \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.51,0:07:04.71,Default,,0,0,0,,“so as not to see death, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.71,0:07:06.78,Default,,0,0,0,,“and he was nowhere to be found \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.78,0:07:09.45,Default,,0,0,0,,“because God had transferred him; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.45,0:07:11.55,Default,,0,0,0,,“for before he was transferred \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.55,0:07:13.55,Default,,0,0,0,,“he received the witness \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.55,0:07:16.25,Default,,0,0,0,,that he had pleased God well.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.25,0:07:19.62,Default,,0,0,0,,The book of Jude, verses 14 and 15, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.62,0:07:22.83,Default,,0,0,0,,informs us that Enoch boldly proclaimed \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.83,0:07:24.86,Default,,0,0,0,,that Jehovah was going to destroy \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.86,0:07:27.46,Default,,0,0,0,,that ungodly world. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.46,0:07:30.17,Default,,0,0,0,,It appears that wicked, violent men \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.17,0:07:32.17,Default,,0,0,0,,were going to take Enoch’s life \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.17,0:07:34.17,Default,,0,0,0,,because of his bold witness. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.17,0:07:36.94,Default,,0,0,0,,So God chose to take him\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.94,0:07:39.98,Default,,0,0,0,,—that is, gently cutting short his life, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.98,0:07:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,sparing him the pangs of a violent death.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.75,0:07:46.98,Default,,0,0,0,,In modern times, like Enoch, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.98,0:07:48.99,Default,,0,0,0,,many brothers and sisters \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.99,0:07:51.59,Default,,0,0,0,,have boldly declared God’s judgments \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.59,0:07:54.56,Default,,0,0,0,,even when faced with death. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.56,0:07:57.03,Default,,0,0,0,,One brother, \Nafter receiving a death sentence \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.03,0:07:59.90,Default,,0,0,0,,at Nazi hands during World War II, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.90,0:08:03.80,Default,,0,0,0,,wrote these words \Nshortly before his execution: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.80,0:08:08.70,Default,,0,0,0,,“I have such peace, such tranquillity, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.70,0:08:12.01,Default,,0,0,0,,that you can’t possibly imagine!” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.01,0:08:14.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Faith made such boldness \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.68,0:08:16.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and calmness possible. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.88,0:08:19.38,Default,,0,0,0,,In many ways, you very likely \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.38,0:08:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,have shown the same faith as Enoch. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.19,0:08:27.06,Default,,0,0,0,,By faith, \Nyou stand up to an ungodly world \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.06,0:08:30.19,Default,,0,0,0,,by not adopting its corrupt ways. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.19,0:08:33.86,Default,,0,0,0,,By faith, \Nyou boldly declare God’s Word \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.86,0:08:36.80,Default,,0,0,0,,from house to house \Nand in public places. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.80,0:08:39.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Before you became a baptized Witness, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.57,0:08:43.07,Default,,0,0,0,,you may have thought you would never do \Nthis preaching work! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.07,0:08:45.07,Default,,0,0,0,,But you are doing it, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.07,0:08:47.08,Default,,0,0,0,,sometimes even in the face \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.08,0:08:49.48,Default,,0,0,0,,of verbal abuse and opposition. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.48,0:08:52.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Faith has made it happen.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.58,0:08:55.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s read verse 7: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.22,0:08:57.75,Default,,0,0,0,,“By faith Noah, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.75,0:09:01.42,Default,,0,0,0,,“after receiving divine warning \Nof things not yet seen, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.42,0:09:04.86,Default,,0,0,0,,“showed godly fear \Nand constructed an ark \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.86,0:09:07.23,Default,,0,0,0,,“for the saving of his household; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.23,0:09:10.43,Default,,0,0,0,,“and through this faith \Nhe condemned the world, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.43,0:09:12.90,Default,,0,0,0,,“and he became an heir \Nof the righteousness \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.90,0:09:14.87,Default,,0,0,0,,that results from faith.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.87,0:09:17.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing in the Bible indicates \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.67,0:09:20.54,Default,,0,0,0,,that Jehovah chose Noah \Nto construct an ark \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.54,0:09:23.58,Default,,0,0,0,,because he was an experienced builder. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.58,0:09:27.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Certainly, he never had built \Nsuch a gigantic vessel \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.72,0:09:30.69,Default,,0,0,0,,as what Jehovah \Nhad asked him to construct. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.69,0:09:34.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Noah likely pondered many questions:\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.32,0:09:37.23,Default,,0,0,0,, ‘How will I get all the building materials? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.23,0:09:40.50,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Do I have the right tools to do the job? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.50,0:09:43.23,Default,,0,0,0,,‘How will I gather all the animals? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.23,0:09:46.27,Default,,0,0,0,,‘What food will they need, and how much? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.27,0:09:49.97,Default,,0,0,0,,‘When, exactly, will the Deluge begin? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.97,0:09:52.07,Default,,0,0,0,,‘How long will it last? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.07,0:09:55.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Where will the ark land \Nafter the Flood subsides?’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.81,0:09:58.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing in the record indicates \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.35,0:10:01.85,Default,,0,0,0,,that Jehovah gave Noah \Nall the details in advance. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.85,0:10:05.29,Default,,0,0,0,,What Noah did have was faith. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.29,0:10:08.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Faith moved him to begin building. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.02,0:10:11.59,Default,,0,0,0,,His faith saved him and his family. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.59,0:10:15.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Faith in Jehovah made it happen.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.63,0:10:19.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Like Noah, during this time of the end, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.07,0:10:21.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah’s people have taken on \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.34,0:10:24.54,Default,,0,0,0,,challenging theocratic building projects. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.54,0:10:27.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Certainly, constructing \Nthe new world headquarters \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.38,0:10:29.25,Default,,0,0,0,,at Warwick, New York, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.25,0:10:32.62,Default,,0,0,0,,was one of these projects \Nthat required much faith. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.62,0:10:34.92,Default,,0,0,0,,A committee of brothers was assigned \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.92,0:10:37.09,Default,,0,0,0,,to complete this vast project \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.09,0:10:39.09,Default,,0,0,0,,in less than four years. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.09,0:10:42.16,Default,,0,0,0,,To do so, they knew they had to begin \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.16,0:10:45.03,Default,,0,0,0,,by July 2013. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.03,0:10:47.76,Default,,0,0,0,,They moved ahead in faith. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.76,0:10:51.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Though the town \Nhad not yet approved the site permits, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.60,0:10:54.20,Default,,0,0,0,,they began inviting workers to the site \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.20,0:10:57.04,Default,,0,0,0,,with that date in mind. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.04,0:10:59.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Time was passing quickly. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.08,0:11:02.78,Default,,0,0,0,,The invited volunteers \Nwere buying plane tickets. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.78,0:11:06.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Bethel was arranging rooming \Nand other details. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.75,0:11:10.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Yet, the committee \Nstill did not have site permits. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.32,0:11:12.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Would they cancel these invitations? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.89,0:11:15.29,Default,,0,0,0,,They state: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.29,0:11:18.19,Default,,0,0,0,,“We spent a lot of time praying about it. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.19,0:11:21.63,Default,,0,0,0,,“We decided we needed to act in faith. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.63,0:11:24.03,Default,,0,0,0,,“And we were just convinced \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.03,0:11:26.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah was going to make it happen.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.87,0:11:29.54,Default,,0,0,0,,As the deadline approached, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.54,0:11:32.01,Default,,0,0,0,,the brothers had done everything possible \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.01,0:11:34.04,Default,,0,0,0,,to obtain the permits. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.04,0:11:38.11,Default,,0,0,0,,The town planning board \Nwas holding a public hearing. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.11,0:11:40.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And to the brothers’ great surprise, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.78,0:11:43.85,Default,,0,0,0,,within 15 minutes \Nof the start of the meeting, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.85,0:11:47.22,Default,,0,0,0,,the town board voted \Nto approve the project. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.22,0:11:50.66,Default,,0,0,0,,These overseers commented, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.66,0:11:53.40,Default,,0,0,0,,“When the approval came through, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.40,0:11:56.50,Default,,0,0,0,,“we knew it was \Nonly by Jehovah’s spirit \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.50,0:11:58.37,Default,,0,0,0,,that that happened.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.37,0:12:01.80,Default,,0,0,0,,True, but it was \Nalso the brothers’ faith \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.80,0:12:04.61,Default,,0,0,0,,to act that made it happen. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.61,0:12:07.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Those experiences \Nare found in the video \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.84,0:12:11.71,Default,,0,0,0,,World Headquarters\N—History Is Being Written. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.71,0:12:15.05,Default,,0,0,0,,You can find it \Nin the “Our Activities” section \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.05,0:12:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,under the “Construction” category.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.02,0:12:23.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Now let’s read Hebrews 11:8: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.03,0:12:27.20,Default,,0,0,0,,“By faith Abraham, when he was called, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.20,0:12:29.33,Default,,0,0,0,,“obeyed by going out to a place \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.33,0:12:32.20,Default,,0,0,0,,“he was to receive as an inheritance; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.20,0:12:34.90,Default,,0,0,0,,“he went out, although not knowing \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.90,0:12:36.74,Default,,0,0,0,,where he was going.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.74,0:12:38.77,Default,,0,0,0,,What faith it took \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.77,0:12:41.74,Default,,0,0,0,,for Abraham \Nand his submissive wife, Sarah, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.74,0:12:44.38,Default,,0,0,0,,to leave the prosperous city of Ur \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.38,0:12:47.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and to go wherever \NJehovah would lead them! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.55,0:12:51.02,Default,,0,0,0,,It meant leaving the security \Nof a pleasant home \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.02,0:12:55.39,Default,,0,0,0,,and moving to some strange \Nand potentially hostile land \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.39,0:13:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,some 1,000 miles, \Nor 1,609 kilometers,  away.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.43,0:13:03.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Do we see such faith today? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.70,0:13:05.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Absolutely! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.70,0:13:07.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Since 2014, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.77,0:13:09.87,Default,,0,0,0,,thousands of brothers and sisters \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.87,0:13:12.81,Default,,0,0,0,,have attended the School \Nfor Kingdom Evangelizers, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.81,0:13:15.44,Default,,0,0,0,,agreeing to be assigned \Nto wherever \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.44,0:13:18.01,Default,,0,0,0,,there is a need \Nby the organization. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.01,0:13:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Faith has made it happen. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.08,0:13:24.95,Default,,0,0,0,,When a call goes out \Nfor skilled volunteers \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.95,0:13:28.36,Default,,0,0,0,,to help build \Nor expand branch facilities, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.36,0:13:32.96,Default,,0,0,0,,faith moves brothers and sisters \Nto simplify their lives \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.96,0:13:36.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and to leave their comfort zone \Nin order to assist. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.63,0:13:40.14,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, in 2009, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.14,0:13:43.54,Default,,0,0,0,,the congregations \Nin the United States were informed \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.54,0:13:46.98,Default,,0,0,0,,that an expansion project \Nat Wallkill, New York, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.98,0:13:49.04,Default,,0,0,0,,was being planned. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.04,0:13:52.21,Default,,0,0,0,,One couple moved out \Nof their newly built \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.21,0:13:57.75,Default,,0,0,0,,2,200-square-foot, \Nor 200-square-meter, dream home \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.75,0:14:02.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and into a 270-square-foot, \Nor 25-square-meter, apartment \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.76,0:14:05.43,Default,,0,0,0,,so that they could make \Nthemselves available. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.43,0:14:07.43,Default,,0,0,0,,What happened? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.43,0:14:08.93,Default,,0,0,0,,They explain: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.93,0:14:12.47,Default,,0,0,0,,“One month after we moved \Ninto our small apartment, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.47,0:14:14.97,Default,,0,0,0,,“we received an invitation to serve \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.97,0:14:18.04,Default,,0,0,0,,“as temporary volunteers at Wallkill. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.04,0:14:22.11,Default,,0,0,0,,“It was clear to us \Nthat by simplifying our life, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.11,0:14:25.65,Default,,0,0,0,,we had given Jehovah \Nsomething to bless.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.65,0:14:29.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Faith made it happen for them.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.18,0:14:33.19,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what have we learned today? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.19,0:14:37.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Faith in Jehovah God \Nis a powerful motivating force \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.89,0:14:41.43,Default,,0,0,0,,that impels us to act \Nin harmony with his will. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.43,0:14:44.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah rewards such faith. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.10,0:14:48.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember, the very meaning \Nof the name of our God, Jehovah, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.84,0:14:51.87,Default,,0,0,0,,is “He Causes to Become.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.87,0:14:56.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Truly, he is a God \Nwho makes things happen! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.08,0:15:00.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Brothers and sisters, \Nlet us continue to act in faith. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.98,0:15:03.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah will continue \Nto make wonderful things \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.75,0:15:06.16,Default,,0,0,0,,happen in our personal life. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.16,0:15:09.16,Default,,0,0,0,,We will accomplish things \Nwe never could do \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.16,0:15:11.39,Default,,0,0,0,,through our own personal efforts. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.39,0:15:14.43,Default,,0,0,0,,We will be able to do more \Nin Jehovah’s service. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.43,0:15:16.48,Default,,0,0,0,,May it happen to you \N“according to your faith.”\N
